items.name: Easings
items.content:
# ===================================================================
#
#   Script: Easings
#
#   $$COPYRIGHT$$
#
# ===================================================================

###*
* Holds different easing types and helper methods.
*
* @module gs
* @class Easings
* @memberof gs
* @constructor
###  
class Easings
    @initialize: ->
        ###*
        * Contains all easing functions by type and in/out.
        * @property EASE_FUNCTIONS
        * @type Function[][]
        * @static
        * @final
        ###
        @EASE_FUNCTIONS = [[Math.linearTween, Math.linearTween, Math.linearTween], 
                     [Math.easeOutQuad, Math.easeInQuad, Math.easeInOutQuad], 
                     [Math.easeOutCubic, Math.easeInCubic, Math.easeInOutCubic], 
                     [Math.easeOutQuart, Math.easeInQuart, Math.easeInOutQuart],
                     [Math.easeOutQuint, Math.easeInQuint, Math.easeInOutQuint],
                     [Math.easeOutSine, Math.easeInSine, Math.easeInOutSine],
                     [Math.easeOutExpo, Math.easeInExpo, Math.easeInOutExpo],
                     [Math.easeOutCirc, Math.easeInCirc, Math.easeInOutCirc]]
        
        ###*
        * @property BY_INDEX
        * @type number[][]
        * @static
        * @final
        ###             
        @BY_INDEX = [[[0, 0], [0, 0], [0, 0]], 
                     [[1, 0], [1, 1], [1, 2]],
                     [[2, 0], [2, 1], [2, 2]],
                     [[3, 0], [3, 1], [3, 2]],
                     [[4, 0], [4, 1], [4, 2]],
                     [[5, 0], [5, 1], [5, 2]],
                     [[6, 0], [6, 1], [6, 2]],
                     [[7, 0], [7, 1], [7, 2]]]
         
        ###*
        * @property BY_STRING
        * @type Object
        * @static
        * @final
        ###               
        @BY_STRING = {
            "linear_in": [0, 0], "linear_out": [0, 0], "linear_inout": [0, 0],
            "quad_out": [1, 0], "quad_in": [1, 1], "quad_inout": [1, 2],
            "cubic_out": [2, 0], "cubic_in": [2, 1], "cubic_inout": [2, 2],
            "quart_out": [3, 0], "quart_in": [3, 1], "quart_inout": [3, 2],
            "quint_out": [4, 0], "quint_in": [4, 1], "quint_inout": [4, 2],
            "sine_out": [5, 0], "sine_in": [5, 1], "sine_inout": [5, 2],
            "expo_out": [6, 0], "expo_in": [6, 1], "expo_inout": [6, 2],
            "circ_out": [7, 0], "circ_in": [7, 1], "circ_inout": [7, 2]
        }
        
        ###*
        * @property EASE_LINEAR
        * @type number[][]
        * @static
        * @final
        ###  
        @EASE_LINEAR = @BY_INDEX[gs.EasingTypes.EASE_LINEAR]
        
        ###*
        * @property EASE_QUADRATIC
        * @type number[][]
        * @static
        * @final
        ###  
        @EASE_QUADRATIC = @BY_INDEX[gs.EasingTypes.EASE_QUADRATIC]
        ###*
        * @property EASE_CUBIC
        * @type number[][]
        * @static
        * @final
        ###  
        @EASE_CUBIC = @BY_INDEX[gs.EasingTypes.EASE_CUBIC]
        ###*
        * @property EASE_QUARTIC
        * @type number[][]
        * @static
        * @final
        ###  
        @EASE_QUARTIC = @BY_INDEX[gs.EasingTypes.EASE_QUARTIC]
        ###*
        * @property EASE_QUINTIC
        * @type number[][]
        * @static
        * @final
        ###  
        @EASE_QUINTIC = @BY_INDEX[gs.EasingTypes.EASE_QUINTIC]
        ###*
        * @property EASE_SINUSOIDAL
        * @type number[][]
        * @static
        * @final
        ###  
        @EASE_SINUSOIDAL = @BY_INDEX[gs.EasingTypes.EASE_SINUSOIDAL]
        ###*
        * @property EASE_EXPONENTIAL
        * @type number[][]
        * @static
        * @final
        ###  
        @EASE_EXPONENTIAL = @BY_INDEX[gs.EasingTypes.EASE_EXPONENTIAL]
        ###*
        * @property EASE_CIRCULAR
        * @type number[][]
        * @static
        * @final
        ###  
        @EASE_CIRCULAR = @BY_INDEX[gs.EasingTypes.EASE_CIRCULAR]
    
    ###*
    * @method fromValues
    * @param {number} index - The index.
    * @param {number} inOut - The in-out value.
    ###
    @fromValues: (index, inOut) -> gs.Easings.BY_INDEX[index][inOut]
    
    ###*
    * @method fromObject
    * @param {Object} obj - The easing data-object.
    ###
    @fromObject: (obj, flags, defaults) -> gs.Easings.BY_INDEX[obj.type][obj.inOut]
    
    ###*
    * @method fromString
    * @param {String} s - The easing string like "quad_in" for example.
    ###
    @fromString: (s) -> gs.Easings.BY_STRING[s || "linear_inout"]
    
Easings.initialize()
gs.Easings = Easings
